FBIS3-53759 "drnes012_l_94009" FBIS-NES-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Three Injured in Hebron as `Hundreds' Attack IDF TA1801162494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 18 Jan 94 TA1801162494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] This evening, three residents were injured by IDF [Israel Defense Forces] fire in Hebron after an IDF unit came under a barrage of rocks near the Muslim college in the city. The three suffered moderate to serious wounds. Our correspondent Ron Nesi'el reports that hundreds of residents took part in the riot. The incident took place near a mourning tent, erected last weekend after four Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] terrorists were killed in a gunfight with the IDF.
